{
  "model": "unknown",
  "total_claims": 40,
  "claims": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "text": "The EFE relate the geometry of spacetime to the distribution of mass and energy: R_{\u03bc\u03bd} - (1/2)R g_{\u03bc\u03bd} = (8\u03c0G/c\u2074) T_{\u03bc\u03bd}",
      "type": "definition",
      "provenance": "cited",
      "depends_on": [],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "R_{\u03bc\u03bd} is the Ricci curvature tensor, R is the Ricci scalar, g_{\u03bc\u03bd} is the metric tensor, G is the gravitational constant, c is the speed of light, and T_{\u03bc\u03bd} is the stress-energy tensor.",
      "type": "definition",
      "provenance": "cited",
      "depends_on": [
        1
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "We are finding the metric outside the mass, so there is no matter or energy present. Therefore, T_{\u03bc\u03bd} = 0.",
      "type": "assumption",
      "provenance": "asserted",
      "depends_on": [],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Taking the trace of the EFE in vacuum yields R = 0.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        1,
        3
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The vacuum EFE simplify to R_{\u03bc\u03bd} = 0.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        1,
        3,
        4
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "The spacetime must be invariant under spatial rotations.",
      "type": "assumption",
      "provenance": "asserted",
      "depends_on": [],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "text": "The most general spherically symmetric metric in coordinates (t, r, \u03b8, \u03c6) can be written as ds\u00b2 = -e^{2\u03bd(t,r)} c\u00b2 dt\u00b2 + e^{2\u03bb(t,r)} dr\u00b2 + r\u00b2(d\u03b8\u00b2 + sin\u00b2\u03b8 d\u03c6\u00b2)",
      "type": "invocation_of_known_result",
      "provenance": "cited",
      "depends_on": [
        6
      ],
      "notes": "This is the standard form after choosing areal radius coordinate."
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "text": "We use the metric signature (-, +, +, +).",
      "type": "assumption",
      "provenance": "asserted",
      "depends_on": [],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "text": "For a spherically symmetric vacuum solution, Birkhoff's theorem guarantees that the metric is static (independent of time t) and that cross-terms (like dt dr) can be eliminated.",
      "type": "invocation_of_known_result",
      "provenance": "cited",
      "depends_on": [
        5,
        6
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "text": "Therefore, \u03bd and \u03bb are functions of r only: ds\u00b2 = -e^{2\u03bd(r)} c\u00b2 dt\u00b2 + e^{2\u03bb(r)} dr\u00b2 + r\u00b2(d\u03b8\u00b2 + sin\u00b2\u03b8 d\u03c6\u00b2)",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        7,
        9
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "text": "The Christoffel symbols are defined as \u0393^\u03c1_{\u03bc\u03bd} = (1/2) g^{\u03c1\u03c3}(\u2202_\u03bc g_{\u03bd\u03c3} + \u2202_\u03bd g_{\u03bc\u03c3} - \u2202_\u03c3 g_{\u03bc\u03bd})",
      "type": "definition",
      "provenance": "cited",
      "depends_on": [],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "text": "The non-zero metric components are g_{tt} = -e^{2\u03bd}c\u00b2, g_{rr} = e^{2\u03bb}, g_{\u03b8\u03b8} = r\u00b2, and g_{\u03c6\u03c6} = r\u00b2sin\u00b2\u03b8.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        10
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "text": "Their inverses are simply 1/g_{\u03bc\u03bc}.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        12
      ],
      "notes": "Valid because metric is diagonal."
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "text": "\u0393^t_{tr} = \u0393^t_{rt} = (1/2) g^{tt} \u2202_r g_{tt} = \u03bd'",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        11,
        12,
        13
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "text": "\u0393^r_{tt} = -(1/2) g^{rr} \u2202_r g_{tt} = c\u00b2 \u03bd' e^{2(\u03bd-\u03bb)}",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        11,
        12,
        13
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "text": "\u0393^r_{rr} = (1/2) g^{rr} \u2202_r g_{rr} = \u03bb'",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        11,
        12,
        13
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "text": "\u0393^r_{\u03b8\u03b8} = -(1/2) g^{rr} \u2202_r g_{\u03b8\u03b8} = -r e^{-2\u03bb}",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        11,
        12,
        13
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "text": "\u0393^r_{\u03c6\u03c6} = -(1/2) g^{rr} \u2202_r g_{\u03c6\u03c6} = -r sin\u00b2\u03b8 e^{-2\u03bb}",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        11,
        12,
        13
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "text": "\u0393^\u03b8_{r\u03b8} = \u0393^\u03b8_{\u03b8r} = (1/2) g^{\u03b8\u03b8} \u2202_r g_{\u03b8\u03b8} = 1/r",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        11,
        12,
        13
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 20,
      "text": "\u0393^\u03b8_{\u03c6\u03c6} = -(1/2) g^{\u03b8\u03b8} \u2202_\u03b8 g_{\u03c6\u03c6} = -sin\u03b8 cos\u03b8",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        11,
        12,
        13
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "text": "\u0393^\u03c6_{r\u03c6} = \u0393^\u03c6_{\u03c6r} = (1/2) g^{\u03c6\u03c6} \u2202_r g_{\u03c6\u03c6} = 1/r",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        11,
        12,
        13
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "text": "\u0393^\u03c6_{\u03b8\u03c6} = \u0393^\u03c6_{\u03c6\u03b8} = (1/2) g^{\u03c6\u03c6} \u2202_\u03b8 g_{\u03c6\u03c6} = cot\u03b8",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        11,
        12,
        13
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "text": "The Ricci tensor is given by R_{\u03bc\u03bd} = \u2202_\u03c1 \u0393^\u03c1_{\u03bc\u03bd} - \u2202_\u03bd \u0393^\u03c1_{\u03bc\u03c1} + \u0393^\u03c1_{\u03c1\u03c3} \u0393^\u03c3_{\u03bc\u03bd} - \u0393^\u03c1_{\u03bd\u03c3} \u0393^\u03c3_{\u03bc\u03c1}",
      "type": "definition",
      "provenance": "cited",
      "depends_on": [],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "text": "We only need to evaluate R_{tt}, R_{rr}, and R_{\u03b8\u03b8} (since R_{\u03c6\u03c6} = R_{\u03b8\u03b8} sin\u00b2\u03b8 by symmetry).",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "asserted",
      "depends_on": [
        10,
        23
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 25,
      "text": "R_{tt} = \u2202_r \u0393^r_{tt} + \u0393^r_{tt}(\u0393^t_{tr} + \u0393^r_{rr} + \u0393^\u03b8_{r\u03b8} + \u0393^\u03c6_{r\u03c6}) - 2\u0393^t_{tr}\u0393^r_{tt}",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        14,
        15,
        16,
        19,
        21,
        23
      ],
      "notes": "Intermediate expansion of Ricci tensor formula for tt component."
    },
    {
      "id": 26,
      "text": "R_{tt} = c\u00b2 e^{2(\u03bd-\u03bb)} (\u03bd'' + (\u03bd')\u00b2 - \u03bd'\u03bb' + (2/r)\u03bd')",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        25,
        14,
        15,
        16,
        19,
        21
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 27,
      "text": "R_{rr} = -\u2202_r(\u0393^t_{tr} + \u0393^\u03b8_{r\u03b8} + \u0393^\u03c6_{r\u03c6}) + \u2202_r \u0393^r_{rr} + \u0393^r_{rr}(\u0393^t_{...)",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        14,
        16,
        19,
        21,
        23
      ],
      "notes": "Answer is truncated here; R_{rr} computation incomplete."
    }
  ]
}